Package exe.bbllw8.either

package exe.bbllw8.either
This package provides the Either and Try types.

Either is a type that represents a value of one of two possible types (disjoint union). An instance of Either is an instance of either Left or Right.

The Try type represents a computation that may either result in an exception, or return a successfully computed value. It's similar to, but semantically different from the Either type. Instances of Try, are either an instance of Success or Failure.

Since:
1.0.0
